article.headline: Morgan leads FIU to 36-17 win over Rice
article.description: James Morgan passed for 229 yards and two touchdowns, Maurice Alexander raced 51 yards for a score and Jose Borregales kicked three field goals as Florida International breezed to a 36-17 victory over Rice in Conference USA action on Saturday night.
article.linkText: Morgan leads FIU to 36-17 win over Rice

images.name: FIU picks off Marshman
images.caption: LB Edwin Freeman jumps in front of Evan Marshman's pass and makes the interception to set up the Golden Panthers in Rice territory.

video.headline: FIU picks off Marshman
video.caption: LB Edwin Freeman jumps in front of Evan Marshman's pass and makes the interception to set up the Golden Panthers in Rice territory.
video.title: FIU picks off Marshman
video.description: LB Edwin Freeman jumps in front of Evan Marshman's pass and makes the interception to set up the Golden Panthers in Rice territory.

article.story: MIAMI -- James Morgan passed for 229 yards and two touchdowns, Maurice Alexander raced 51 yards for a score and Jose Borregales kicked three field goals as Florida International breezed to a 36-17 victory over Rice in Conference USA action on Saturday night. Evan Marshman's 7-yard TD run gave Rice a 7-0 lead at the end of the first quarter, but the Panthers (5-2, 3-0) took control in the second quarter. Borregales' 32-yard field goal put FIU on the scoreboard, Alexander followed with his long TD run on the Panthers' next possession and Morgan found Austin Maloney for a 33-yard scoring strike. Borregales missed the extra point and FIU led 16-7. Haden Tobola kicked a 47-yard field goal as time expired in the first half to pull the Owls (1-7, 0-4) within 16-10. FIU's first drive of the third quarter ended with Borregales' 38-yard field goal and Morgan connected with Shemar Thornton for a 29-yard score and a 26-10 lead. Marshman's 22-yard TD run capped the scoring for Rice and left them trailing 26-17 after three quarters. The Panthers put the game out of reach on Morgan's 4-yard TD run and Borregales' 47-yard field goal in the fourth quarter.

videos.headline: FIU jumps ahead with 51-yard TD run
videos.description: WR Maurice Alexander takes the jet sweep and gets to the outside, charging all the way down the sideline and making it 10-7 Golden Panthers.

videos.headline: Rice strikes first with 7-yard QB run
videos.description: Evan Marshman keeps it himself and beats the defense to the end zone to give Owls an early 7-0 lead on the Golden Panthers.

videos.headline: FIU extends lead with 33-yard TD pass
videos.description: QB James Morgan drops a dime to WR Austin Maloney, who brings it in and crosses the goal-line to make it 16-7 Golden Panthers.

videos.headline: FIU QB throws strike for 29-yard TD
videos.description: QB James Morgan puts one in the perfect spot for WR Shemar Thornton, who makes the grab in the end zone and makes it 26-10 Golden Panthers.

videos.headline: Rice QB runs for 2nd TD of game
videos.description: Evan Marshman hurdles a defender and dives for the pylon for a 22-yard touchdown run, cutting the FIU lead to 26-17.

videos.headline: FIU DB lays out for INT
videos.description: Rishard Dames shows off his athleticism with a diving interception and gives the ball back to the Golden Panthers.

videos.headline: FIU puts on exclamation point with 3rd INT
videos.description: DB Isaiah Brown undercuts the pass from Wiley Green and sets up the Golden Panthers for victory formation.
